            <p>The department of physiotherapy was started in the year 2012 initially it wasn't providing much services  and area provided to them in the hospital was also very less. The department has over time expanded to almost full fledged department offering mainly inpatient admissions. This department gives therapy to the patient who r referred from the departments like Neuro, orthopedics, Padietrics... In Neuro:the patients having hemiplegia or paraplegia or paralysis and also stroke patients are treated,In orthopedics: bony injuries and post oparatives are treated and In paediatrics:developmental diseases from birth, cerebral palsy,Neural tube defects, spinal shock, Mylengocoel patients are getting treated. They are provided automated wheel chairs for needy people. </p>
            <p>Daily30-40 patients get the benefits of physiotherapy. We have 4 ICUs in the super speciality.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1.padietrics;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2.neuro;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3.post-operative;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4.nephro.</p>
            <p>In these ICUs, patients with respiratory problems also gets admitted so, the airways blocked due to thick secretions are cleared with the help of therapy.. Chest therapy is also done in this department.</p>
